# Shared variables for container image promotion
# Sourced by scripts/build.sh and referenced in CI
#
# All values can be overridden by environment variables or CI pipeline
# variables. The defaults below are placeholders — set them for your
# environment in CI/CD settings or export before running build.sh.

# ── Pull source (registry proxy / mirror) ────────────────────────────
# Where base images are PULLED FROM. Typically a Harbor/Artifactory/Nexus
# proxy-cache project that fronts Docker Hub, quay.io, etc. Per-image
# SOURCE values reference this as ${PULL_REGISTRY}/docker-hub/...
PULL_REGISTRY="${PULL_REGISTRY:-registry.example.com}"

# ── Push target (QA / dev registry) ──────────────────────────────────
# Where built images are PUSHED TO. Often the same host as PULL_REGISTRY
# when Harbor serves as both proxy-cache and hosted registry.
PUSH_REGISTRY="${PUSH_REGISTRY:-${PULL_REGISTRY}}"
PUSH_PROJECT="${PUSH_PROJECT:-base-images}"

VENDOR="${VENDOR:-example.com}"

# ── Builder image (used for cert injection and CI utility jobs) ──────
# Points to Alpine via the pull proxy — no direct Docker Hub access.
# Override to match your proxy path convention (e.g. docker-hub/library/).
BUILDER_IMAGE="${BUILDER_IMAGE:-${PULL_REGISTRY}/docker-hub/library/alpine:3.21}"

# ── Alpine APK mirror (replaces dl-cdn.alpinelinux.org/alpine) ───────
# Airgapped / semi-airgapped builds should set this to a raw-format
# proxy of https://dl-cdn.alpinelinux.org/alpine so apk fetches don't
# depend on dl-cdn reachability. Version paths (v3.21/main, v3.21/community,
# etc.) are preserved as-is under this base URL.
# Example: APK_MIRROR="https://nexus.example.com/repository/alpine-proxy"
APK_MIRROR="${APK_MIRROR:-}"

# ── Debian / Ubuntu apt mirror ───────────────────────────────────────
# Rewrites /etc/apt/sources.list* inside remediation scripts to route
# apt-get through an apt-proxy group instead of archive.ubuntu.com /
# deb.debian.org. Per-distro path convention is configured in
# scripts/remediate/{debian,ubuntu}.sh — this variable is the proxy base URL.
# The per-distro scripts expect proxy repo names like:
#   ${APT_MIRROR}/apt-debian-<codename>-proxy
#   ${APT_MIRROR}/apt-ubuntu-<codename>-proxy
#   ${APT_MIRROR}/apt-ubuntu-<codename>-ports-proxy   (non-amd64)
# Example: APT_MIRROR="https://nexus.example.com/repository"
APT_MIRROR="${APT_MIRROR:-}"

# ── Production push target (promote destination) ─────────────────────
PROD_PUSH_REGISTRY="${PROD_PUSH_REGISTRY:-prod-registry.example.com}"
PROD_PUSH_PROJECT="${PROD_PUSH_PROJECT:-${PUSH_PROJECT}}"

# ── Optional: registry backend (opt-in enrichment) ───────────────────
# When unset (default), `build.sh --push` runs a plain `docker push` to
# ${PUSH_REGISTRY}/${PUSH_PROJECT}/<image>:<tag> — the Harbor baseline.
# When set to a supported backend, build.sh delegates the push step to
# scripts/push-backends/${REGISTRY_KIND}.sh which handles registry-
# specific enrichment (build info, metadata properties, multi-tenant
# routing). Supported today: artifactory
# REGISTRY_KIND="${REGISTRY_KIND:-}"

# ── Artifactory backend (consumed only when REGISTRY_KIND=artifactory) ─
# ARTIFACTORY_TEAM is intentionally NOT pinned in this file — each
# pipeline / developer exports it so the same repo can push to
# different team repos without committing routing info. The artifactory
# backend hard-fails if it's unset at runtime.
# ARTIFACTORY_URL="${ARTIFACTORY_URL:-https://artifactory.example.com}"
# ARTIFACTORY_USER="${ARTIFACTORY_USER:-}"
# ARTIFACTORY_TOKEN="${ARTIFACTORY_TOKEN:-}"            # access token (preferred)
# ARTIFACTORY_PASSWORD="${ARTIFACTORY_PASSWORD:-}"      # or a basic-auth password
# ARTIFACTORY_TEAM="${ARTIFACTORY_TEAM:-}"              # your 4-letter team acronym (REQUIRED at runtime)
# ARTIFACTORY_ENVIRONMENT="${ARTIFACTORY_ENVIRONMENT:-dev}"  # dev|prod — used by some layout templates below
# ARTIFACTORY_BUILD_NAME="${ARTIFACTORY_BUILD_NAME:-}"       # defaults to image name
# ARTIFACTORY_BUILD_NUMBER="${ARTIFACTORY_BUILD_NUMBER:-}"   # defaults to CI job id / pipeline id / timestamp
# ARTIFACTORY_PROPERTIES="${ARTIFACTORY_PROPERTIES:-}"       # extra ;-separated props, e.g.
#                                                           #   "security.scan=pending;hardened=false"

# ── Artifactory layout templates (nothing hardcoded in the backend) ──
#
# The artifactory backend computes the docker push URL and the REST
# API storage path from two shell-parameter-expansion templates.
# Uncomment the preset that matches your Artifactory layout, or write
# your own. The backend never references a hardcoded repo name —
# everything you see below is what the backend actually resolves at
# runtime. No hidden strings in the .sh files.
#
# Variables available inside the templates:
#   ${ARTIFACTORY_PUSH_HOST}    docker push host (see layouts below)
#   ${ARTIFACTORY_TEAM}         runtime team acronym
#   ${ARTIFACTORY_ENVIRONMENT}  dev|prod — may be unreferenced in layouts
#                               that don't split dev/prod
#   ${ARTIFACTORY_REPO_SUFFIX}  dev→local, prod→prod (legacy convenience
#                               used by the fallback default below)
#   ${IMAGE_NAME}               image short name (e.g. nginx)
#   ${IMAGE_TAG}                computed tag (upstream + git sha)
#
# When nothing is uncommented below, the backend falls back to Layout A
# so existing homelab configurations keep working untouched.

# ── Layout A: Per-team repos (current homelab default) ────────────
#
#   Docker push:  <artifactory-host>/<team>/<image>:<tag>
#   Storage:      <team>-docker-<suffix>/<image>/<tag>/manifest.json
#                 (suffix = "local" when env=dev, "prod" when env=prod)
#
#   Example with team=abcd, env=dev, image=nginx:
#     push URL:       artifactory.example.com/abcd/nginx:1.29.8-<sha>
#     storage path:   abcd-docker-local/nginx/1.29.8-<sha>/manifest.json
#
#   Suits: legacy Artifactory with per-team hosted repos, strong team
#          isolation via repo-level RBAC, per-team retention policies.
#
# ARTIFACTORY_IMAGE_REF='${ARTIFACTORY_PUSH_HOST}/${ARTIFACTORY_TEAM}/${IMAGE_NAME}:${IMAGE_TAG}'
# ARTIFACTORY_MANIFEST_PATH='${ARTIFACTORY_TEAM}-docker-${ARTIFACTORY_REPO_SUFFIX}/${IMAGE_NAME}/${IMAGE_TAG}/manifest.json'

# ── Layout B: Shared repo with team folder (path-routed) ──────────
#
#   Docker push:  <artifactory-host>/<repo>/<team>/<image>:<tag>
#   Storage:      <repo>/<team>/<image>/<tag>/manifest.json
#
#   Example with repo=docker, team=abcd, image=nginx:
#     push URL:       artifactory.example.com/docker/abcd/nginx:1.29.8-<sha>
#     storage path:   docker/abcd/nginx/1.29.8-<sha>/manifest.json
#
#   Suits: one shared hosted repo, teams separated by folder path,
#          RBAC via pattern-based permission targets.
#          Replace 'docker' with whatever your backing repo is called.
#
# ARTIFACTORY_IMAGE_REF='${ARTIFACTORY_PUSH_HOST}/docker/${ARTIFACTORY_TEAM}/${IMAGE_NAME}:${IMAGE_TAG}'
# ARTIFACTORY_MANIFEST_PATH='docker/${ARTIFACTORY_TEAM}/${IMAGE_NAME}/${IMAGE_TAG}/manifest.json'

# ── Layout C: Subdomain-routed shared repo (JFrog recommended) ────
#
#   RECOMMENDED by JFrog as of 2024 for Docker at scale. Uses
#   Artifactory's reverse-proxy subdomain routing so the docker push
#   URL has no repo-name prefix — cleaner URLs, fewer docker v2 API
#   edge cases, and separate DNS names for push vs pull proxies.
#
#   DNS you'll need (ops / platform team sets up):
#     docker.artifactory.example.com       → backing repo "docker"
#     dockerhub.artifactory.example.com    → backing proxy "docker-hub"
#
#   Docker push:  docker.artifactory.example.com/<team>/<image>:<tag>
#   Storage:      <repo>/<team>/<image>/<tag>/manifest.json
#
#   Example with team=abcd, image=nginx, repo=docker:
#     push URL:       docker.artifactory.example.com/abcd/nginx:1.29.8-<sha>
#     storage path:   docker/abcd/nginx/1.29.8-<sha>/manifest.json
#
#   This layout does NOT reference ${ARTIFACTORY_ENVIRONMENT} in
#   either template, so orgs with no dev/prod split (one shared
#   `docker` repo for all builds) just work. If you want dev/prod
#   later, either add an ENVIRONMENT segment to the path or use
#   separate `docker-dev` / `docker-prod` backing repos and template
#   on ${ARTIFACTORY_ENVIRONMENT}.
#
# ARTIFACTORY_PUSH_HOST="docker.artifactory.example.com"
# ARTIFACTORY_IMAGE_REF='${ARTIFACTORY_PUSH_HOST}/${ARTIFACTORY_TEAM}/${IMAGE_NAME}:${IMAGE_TAG}'
# ARTIFACTORY_MANIFEST_PATH='docker/${ARTIFACTORY_TEAM}/${IMAGE_NAME}/${IMAGE_TAG}/manifest.json'

# ── Layout D: Subdomain-per-team (strongest isolation) ────────────
#
#   Each team has its own subdomain pointing at its own repo.
#
#   Docker push:  <team>.artifactory.example.com/<image>:<tag>
#   Storage:      <team>-docker-<suffix>/<image>/<tag>/manifest.json
#
#   Example with team=abcd, env=dev, image=nginx:
#     push URL:       abcd.artifactory.example.com/nginx:1.29.8-<sha>
#     storage path:   abcd-docker-local/nginx/1.29.8-<sha>/manifest.json
#
#   Suits: enterprise with DNS-per-team, strict isolation policies,
#          one Artifactory with many teams that must not see each
#          other's URLs.
#
# ARTIFACTORY_PUSH_HOST='${ARTIFACTORY_TEAM}.artifactory.example.com'
# ARTIFACTORY_IMAGE_REF='${ARTIFACTORY_PUSH_HOST}/${IMAGE_NAME}:${IMAGE_TAG}'
# ARTIFACTORY_MANIFEST_PATH='${ARTIFACTORY_TEAM}-docker-${ARTIFACTORY_REPO_SUFFIX}/${IMAGE_NAME}/${IMAGE_TAG}/manifest.json'

# ── Layout E: Team-dispatch subdomain (homelab default) ───────────
#
#   One shared `docker.*` subdomain dispatches to per-team repos
#   based on the first path segment. A reverse-proxy sidecar (nginx
#   map block) reads the first path segment, routes the request to
#   <team>-docker-local, and STRIPS that segment before it reaches
#   Artifactory — so the team folder does NOT exist in storage.
#
#   Docker push:  docker.artifactory.example.com/<team>/<image>:<tag>
#   Storage:      <team>-docker-<suffix>/<image>/<tag>/manifest.json
#                 (NOTE: no <team> folder under the repo — stripped
#                  by the dispatching proxy)
#
#   Example with team=abcd, env=dev, image=nginx:
#     push URL:       docker.artifactory.example.com/abcd/nginx:1.29.8-<sha>
#     storage path:   abcd-docker-local/nginx/1.29.8-<sha>/manifest.json
#
#   Suits: one clean push hostname for all teams, per-team repo
#          isolation via RBAC, no DNS record per team. Looks like
#          Layout C from the client's POV but stores like Layout A.
#          Requires a reverse-proxy sidecar that does host+path →
#          repo rewriting (JCR's built-in subdomain routing won't do
#          this — needs external nginx).
#
# ARTIFACTORY_PUSH_HOST="docker.artifactory.example.com"
# ARTIFACTORY_IMAGE_REF='${ARTIFACTORY_PUSH_HOST}/${ARTIFACTORY_TEAM}/${IMAGE_NAME}:${IMAGE_TAG}'
# ARTIFACTORY_MANIFEST_PATH='${ARTIFACTORY_TEAM}-docker-${ARTIFACTORY_REPO_SUFFIX}/${IMAGE_NAME}/${IMAGE_TAG}/manifest.json'
